    • Method Detail

      • comparePreference

        int comparePreference(R lhs,
                      R rhs)
        Compare the preferability of one route with anther
        Parameters:
        lhs - 1st route with which to compare preference
        rhs - 2nd route with which to compare preference
        Returns:
        -1 if lhs route is less preferable than rhs; 0 if lhs route and rhs are equally preferable (i.e. for multipath routing); 1 if lhs route is strictly more preferred than rhs

        Returns:

      • longestPrefixMatch

        java.util.Set<R> longestPrefixMatch(Ip address,
                                    int maxPrefixLength)
        Execute a constrained longest prefix match for a given IP address.

        To be used when the longest prefix match is unsatisfactory and less specific route(s) is required.

        Parameters:
        address - the IP address to match
        maxPrefixLength - the maximum prefix length allowed (i.e., do not match more specific routes). This is a less than or equal constraint.
        Returns:
        a set of routes that match the address given the constraint.
